TOBELMANN, Respondent, v. ROPER, Appellant. No. 6791; May 20, 1881. A Street Assessment Lien cannot be Enforced Against Less Than All of the property owners liable therefor.1 APPEAL from Twenty-third District Court, San Francisco.

J. C. Bates for respondent; D. H. Whittemore for appellant.

Cited and distinguished in Parker v. Altschul, 60 Cal. 381, where there was nothing to show that the appellant had objected to a dismissal as to some of the defendants.

 By the COURT.

On the authority of Clark v. Porter, 53 Cal. 409, and Diggins v. Reay; 54 Cal. 525, judgment and order reversed and cause remanded for a new trial.
